89bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg, https://images.food52.com/uZr5yQqzHoOrrecUkiw0Mox22lU=/1536x1878/filters:format(webp)/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\" media=\"(min-width: 500px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/ev9vDdMo8y3NzNT9qrHr-F-_dvw=/768x939/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg, https://images.food52.com/xnNcy3fh5B-vUiEUbGeIgyhE0MQ=/1536x1878/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003csource srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\" type=\"image/webp\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/egU7dIFCgUR26EYzL7cid6r1DVg=/375x458/filters:format(webp)/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg, https://images.food52.com/OdZbZfhwU2upImm8jsfZEdcP9mE=/750x916/filters:format(webp)/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003cimg srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/pqiUsLjlM5tUfhVPBGgcAjnKbAM=/375x458/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg, https://images.food52.com/K5cQvGliOmrVLtu7xc-V1OfPooE=/750x916/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg 2x\" alt=\"\" width=\"964\" height=\"1179\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/pqiUsLjlM5tUfhVPBGgcAjnKbAM=/375x458/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg, https://images.food52.com/K5cQvGliOmrVLtu7xc-V1OfPooE=/750x916/ba51e7eb-f203-4f96-8026-566a589bdb70--Miso_Oatmeal.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by Noah Tanen\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003cp\u003eAs someone who grew up somewhat ambivalent towards oatmeal, my first “aha moment” with the cereal grain came when I had a savory version. I was working as a baker at a commissary kitchen in the Fishtown neighborhood of Philadelphia, not far from \u003ca href=\"https://www.lostbreadco.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eLost Bread Bakery\u003c/a\u003e. For lunch on the weekends, I would slink out of work with my own metal bowl in tow, as Lost Bread admirably didn’t offer to-go containers, and go see what was interesting on the lunch menu. One day, I was served a hot bowl of whole oat groats, cooked in a surprisingly savory broth and served with a marinated egg. It was similar to the Ginger Fried Oat Bowl featured in one of the bakery’s stellar \u003ca href=\"https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5988b9932994ca0cad689333/t/5e46d0d668457b231823b657/1581699294259/LBzine_oatFINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003egrain zines\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \u003cp\u003eThat dish served as the inspiration for my own recipe, which calls for steel-cut oats and miso as a flavor base. If you’re on the fence, it might just convince you to go salty over sweet the next time you crack open the oats.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003cp\u003eIngredients\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \u003ctable role=\"presentation\"\u003e\n              \u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  cup steel-cut oats\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e4\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  cups water\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  tablespoons white miso\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  teaspoon salt, divided\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                   head lacinato kale\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  tablespoon neutral oil\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003csup\u003e1\u003c/sup\u003e/\u003csub\u003e4\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  teaspoon black pepper\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                  tablespoon rice vinegar\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e4\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                   eggs\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                   flaky salt for garnish, optional\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n              \u003ctr\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003ctd\u003e\n                   chili crisp for garnish, optional\n\n                \u003c/td\u003e\n              \u003c/tr\u003e\n          \u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n\n            \u003ctable role=\"presentation\"\u003e\n                \u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    cup steel-cut oats\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e4\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    cups water\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    tablespoons white miso\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    teaspoon salt, divided\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                     head lacinato kale\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    tablespoon neutral oil\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n            \u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n            \u003ctable role=\"presentation\"\u003e\n                \u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003csup\u003e1\u003c/sup\u003e/\u003csub\u003e4\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    teaspoon black pepper\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                    tablespoon rice vinegar\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003cspan\u003e4\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                     eggs\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                     flaky salt for garnish, optional\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n                \u003ctr\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\n                  \u003ctd\u003e\n                     chili crisp for garnish, optional\n\n                  \u003c/td\u003e\n                \u003c/tr\u003e\n            \u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n              \u003chr/\u003e\n\n              \n              \u003ccenter\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eHave you given savory oatmeal a try? I\u0026#39;d love to hear what toppings you\u0026#39;re adding to make it your own.\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/center\u003e\n          \u003c/div\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n            \n            \n\n\n\n            \n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n\n    \u003cp\u003e\n      Test Kitchen Content Creator at Food52\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003ePopular on Food52\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
